OL,3,CLong-term social care reform unlikely
OL,4,Cbefore 2028, government says
OL,6,F"The investment and reforms we're
OL,7,Fannouncing today will help to
OL,8,Fmodernise social care, get it working
OL,9,Fmore closely with the NHS, and help
OL,10,Fdeliver our Plan for Change.
OL,12,F"But our ageing society, with costs of
OL,13,Fcare set to double in the next 20
OL,14,Fyears, demands longer term action.
OL,16,F"The independent commission will work
OL,17,Fto build a national consensus around a
OL,18,Fnew National Care Service able to meet
OL,19,Fthe needs of older and disabled people
OL,20,Finto the 21st century."
