OL,3,CLong-term social care reform unlikely
OL,4,Cbefore 2028, government says
OL,6,FStreeting said he had written to
OL,7,Fopposition parties to take part in the
OL,8,Fcomission's work, and asked Baroness
OL,9,FCasey to "build a cross-party
OL,10,Fconsensus" to ensure the National Care
OL,11,FService's long-term survival.
OL,13,FSarah Woolnough, chief executive at
OL,14,FThe King's Fund, welcomed the
OL,15,Fannouncement, but urged the government
OL,16,Fto "accelerate the timing".
OL,18,F"This could offer a real opportunity
OL,19,Fto break the cycle of failure to
OL,20,Freform social care," she said.
